Powered by an advanced AI proprietary platform, a national network of 1,300 brokers, 230 retail stores, a team of experienced buyer’s agents, integrated property search and conveyancing, Aussie is supporting customers at every step of their property journey to find, buy and own with more confidence than ever before. Lendi Group’s loan book is more than $100b and it was named Australia’s Aggregator of the Year for 2024.

To learn more about life at Lendi Group check out our blog: https://www.lendi.com.au/inspire/category/life-at-lendi/

Why Join Us?

Innovation at Our Core – We challenge the status quo and push boundaries to create better solutions.
Work with the Best – Collaborate with some of the brightest minds in fintech, financial services, and strategy.
Make an Impact – Contribute to meaningful projects that shape our business and the future of property finance.
Grow & Evolve – Develop your skills and advance your career in a fast-moving, purpose-driven environment.

As a Lead Data Scientist, you'll lead a growing data science team and play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering data-driven solutions across stakeholders. Your primary responsibilities include leading and mentoring your team, designing and implementing advanced machine learning and statistical models, translating complex business problems into scalable data products, and leading the end-to-end lifecycle from discovery to production. You will lead by example with modern data science techniques and tooling, providing clear technical direction and coaching to team members. 

We’re looking for a collaborative team player who thrives in a dynamic environment, embraces the challenge of legacy systems, remains composed under pressure, and is driven to deliver continuous improvement and strategic impact.  This role provides a unique opportunity to connect directly with our stakeholders.  You should be a versatile data leader who can both drive hands-on delivery and lead the development of new data initiatives—balancing strategic oversight with practical execution. 

Job Description

On a typical day you will: 
 

Lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (up to10 people) and set the technical direction and standards 
Collaborate within a cross-functional digital team, including Product Management, Engineering and Design. 
Bridge the gap between business problems and data science solutions, turning opportunities into impactful, production-ready models. 
Utilise strong analytical and modelling skills to design, build, and validate machine learning solutions, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), neural networks, and transformer-based approaches. 
Define and lead the end-to-end lifecycle of data products in an agile environment, from problem framing and experimentation through to deployment and monitoring. 
Conduct and document detailed analysis, including business case development, to prioritise use cases and clearly communicate trade-offs and expected value to stakeholders. 
Work closely with data and platform engineers on ETL pipelines, containerised solutions (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes), and cloud-based environments (e.g. GCP, AWS, Azure), with exposure to modern data platforms such as Snowflake and Databricks. 
Collaborate with cross-functional Agile teams (Engineering, Product, Design, QA) in remote and on-site settings, applying appropriate governance and engagement models to data projects. 
Provide BAU support for existing models and data products, while actively managing demand, prioritisation, and stakeholder expectations to create space for strategic, high-impact data science initiatives. 

 

Qualifications
Proven end-to-end Data Science experience (6+ years), including recent experience operating at Senior/Lead level 
Proven ability to lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (typically 3–10 people) and to set technical direction and standards 
Strong, hands-on expertise with modern machine learning models and algorithms, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), statistical models, and neural networks 
Demonstrated experience working with LLMs, transformers and embeddings in practical, production-oriented use cases 
Solid understanding of the end-to-end lifecycle of data products, from problem framing and model development through to productisation, pipelining and BAU support 
Proficiency in Python and a strong command of SQL for data exploration, feature engineering and model implementation 
Experience working with cloud platforms (e.g. GCP, AWS or Azure) and familiarity with modern data ecosystems such as Snowflake and/or Databricks (or ability to upskill quickly) 
Exposure to containerised solutions (e.g. Docker) and collaborating with engineers on production deployment and MLOps practices 
Strong stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to translate business problems into data solutions and tell a compelling story with insights 
Experience contributing to or leading governance and engagement models (e.g. steering committees, RACI/RASCI frameworks, working groups) across multiple stakeholders 
Demonstrated capability in prioritisation and managing tradeoffs in a resourceconstrained or scaleup environment, including pushing back on lowvalue work 
Experience developing or contributing to business cases for data and AI initiatives, including articulating value, risks and assumptions 
Additional Information

Lendi Group teams operate across Australia and the Philippines. Bringing together diverse expertise, innovative technology and a customer-first approach, our teams work seamlessly to simplify the property journey, helping Australians find, buy and own property with confidence.

Generous paid Parental Leave: we celebrate our growing Lendi Group family with 18-26 weeks leave for primary carers and up to 4 weeks for secondary carers.
An additional week’s Loyalty Leave each year after reaching 3 years’ service.
Wellness initiatives with a strong focus on psychological safety.

 

We’re committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive community at Lendi Group. We believe that a team reflecting the world around us leads to greater innovation, stronger collaboration, and a more engaging workplace.

Our culture is guided by our 3 core values: We Are Stronger United; Act Like You Own It; and Keep Home Loans Human. Our values are part of our core DNA that helps Lendi Group to attract, engage and evolve the right talent and build best-in-class products.

This is an opportunity to shape the future of a fast-growing, purpose-driven company that’s transforming the homeownership journey.

Ready to contribute to Lendi Group’s next chapter? Apply now and be part of something big!

eHealth Queensland is one of the largest Information Communication Technology operations in the state. It is responsible for ensuring the smooth operation of information systems and technologies so that Queensland Health employees and health providers have access to information that supports the delivery of health care.

Queensland Health is currently undertaking one of the largest health infrastructure programs ever seen in Australia. The Hospital Rescue Plan will deliver 3 new hospitals, a new Queensland Cancer Centre, and the expansion of 11 existing hospitals resulting in 2,600 additional beds across Queensland.   

This program represents an opportunity for you to make your mark on the future of healthcare and help to shape the future of health centres across Queensland, for Queenslanders for generations to come.

Job Title: Senior Analyst / Manager - Capital & Provision Reporting
Ad Text:
Senior Analyst / Manager – Capital & Provision Reporting

Are you ready to step into a role where your analysis genuinely shapes business decisions and regulatory outcomes?

This is a rare opportunity to join a high-performing Treasury function within a leading financial services organisation. The team sits at the centre of the business, influencing how capital, provisions, liquidity and risk are managed across a diverse banking and financial services portfolio.

You’ll work alongside smart, collaborative people who value clear thinking, curiosity and impact — in an environment where ideas are encouraged and expertise is trusted.

The opportunity as a Senior Analyst / Manager, you’ll play a key role in regulatory capital and financial provision reporting across a broad product suite.

You’ll be responsible for delivering high-quality monthly, quarterly and annual analysis, ensuring complex regulatory and risk concepts are translated into clear, meaningful insights for senior stakeholders.

This is a role for someone who enjoys getting close to the detail and stepping back to see the bigger picture.

You’ll synthesise large datasets, contribute to the evolution of capital, provision and loss modelling frameworks, and support commercial decision-making while balancing risk and regulatory requirements.

You’ll collaborate closely with teams across Treasury, product, credit risk, regulatory data, technology, finance and risk — gaining deep exposure to how a modern, technology-driven bank operates.

What you’ll be doing?
Owning and delivering regulatory capital and financial provision reporting
Producing clear, insightful analysis for business and regulatory stakeholders
Interpreting complex technical and modelling outputs for non-technical audiences
Supporting the development and enhancement of capital, provision and loss models
Applying strategic and commercial thinking to risk and business opportunities
Working collaboratively across multiple teams to drive accurate, timely outcomes
What you’ll bring?
Qualifications in finance, accounting, business, quantitative disciplines or similar
3–6 years’ experience in credit risk, capital, provisioning or financial reporting
Exposure to regulatory capital frameworks and/or financial provision standards
Strong data and analytical capability, ideally with R and/or SQL experience
Commercial mindset, sharp problem-solving skills and strong attention to detail
Excellent communication skills and confidence engaging with senior stakeholders
Why join?

You’ll be part of a supportive, inclusive and intellectually curious environment where careers are built with intention. The organisation is known for investing in its people, encouraging diverse perspectives, and offering meaningful opportunities to grow — both technically and professionally.
Flexible working, strong learning and development support, generous leave options and wellbeing benefits are all part of the package, alongside the chance to work on complex, high-impact problems that really matter.

Job Title: Multiple Lead Vulnerability Assessor & Multiple Senior Vulnerability Assessor
Ad Text:
Multiple Senior Vulnerability Assessors

Role Overview

Vulnerability Assessors identify, assess and prioritise threat vulnerabilities identified through penetration testing and report findings to improve security architecture and enhance risk awareness.

Australian Signals Directorate (ASD) requires multiple APS 6 equivalent Senior Vulnerability Assessors (encompassing Security Specialists; Security Engineers) to fill positions across the agency. 

In addition to filling current vacancies, a merit pool will be created for future positions that may arise within 12 months of RFQ close date. 

Please apply only if you fit the following criteria:

Clearance: This RFQ is for NV2 and TSPV cleared candidates only. 

Location of work: QLD, ACT, VIC

Working arrangements: Onsite

Suitable candidates will be required to undergo ASD's Organisational Suitability Assessment (OSA) prior to commencement and ASD will then allocate successful candidates to business areas based on operational needs. Additional information on the OSA can be found: https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/how-apply/candidate-information

Key duties and responsibilities

Include but not limited to:

Perform forensically sound security investigations on a wide array of assets and devices that directly relate to security infrastructure; in accordance with established procedures. 

Conduct investigations which may be as the result of a security incident or by direction of senior leadership. 

Assess and explain threat profiles of a variety of electronic devices.

Communicate and provide advice and guidance on strategies to improve ASD ICT security and mitigate risk of devices compromising that security. 

Interpret and comply with relevant policy governing ICT security in ASD; both internal and whole of government, including legislation that underpins digital security and online privacy. 

Evaluate and assist with the application and compliance of security controls and review information systems for actual or potential security vulnerabilities. 

Use appropriate system design methods, tools and techniques selecting appropriately from predictive (plan-driven) approaches or adaptive (iterative/agile) approaches and ensure they are applied effectively. 

Design, code, verify, test, document, amend and refactor complex programs/scripts as required. 

Technical skills

Certification in CREST Registered Penetration Tester or CREST Registered Threat Intelligence Analyst desirable.

About the organisation

The Australian Signals Directorate is a statutory agency in the Defence portfolio that defends Australia against global threats and advances our national interests through the provision of foreign signals intelligence, cyber security and offensive cyber operations as directed by the Australian Government.

Criteria

The buyer has specified that each candidate must provide a response to each criterion. Each response is limited to 3000 characters.

Essential criteria

1.Demonstrated experience in undertaking threat intelligence/modelling tasks or threat assessments.

2.Experience undertaking penetration testing and providing insights into vulnerabilities, effectiveness of defences and mitigating controls.

3.Experience in the creation and maintenance of executive and/or business reporting relating to threat assessment analysis and mitigation strategies.

Drive strategic projects involving data ingestion and curation, exploratory data analysis, natural language processing, use of generative AI including agent based generative AI, predictive and prescriptive modelling, deployment of self service solutions and ad hoc data science products.
Prototype and develop engineering solutions at short notice for high priority data science and AI projects.
Coordinate and collaborate with other teams to build internal capability and establish or adopt standards and procedures across the development product life cycle.
Use customer centred approaches to design and prototype new technologies, tools and methods.
Work with IT service providers to specify requirements and support the establishment and upgrade of on premises and cloud infrastructure and tools.
Work closely with business users and IT service providers to select suitable technologies to deliver, manage and improve data science and AI solutions.
Key capabilities
Experience leading data, AI and cloud engineering work within the public sector or a complex multi stakeholder environment.
Experience establishing and maintaining rapport with clients and suppliers, including where there are no pre existing relationships.
Experience designing, implementing and managing relational databases such as Teradata, BigQuery or equivalent platforms.
Experience designing and implementing CI CD pipelines, monitoring systems, containerisation, orchestration and automation.
Experience working in Agile or other iterative delivery environments, including DevOps.
Experience designing and managing cloud infrastructure in Azure, AWS or Google Cloud.
Demonstrated ability to conduct independent research, address knowledge gaps and adopt emerging technologies to deliver innovative solutions.
Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate technical concepts for non technical audiences.
Desirable experience
Experience implementing engineering solutions for generative AI including agent based solutions, prompt engineering and AI output evaluation.
Experience deploying open weight large language models, fine tuning them and integrating them with web applications via APIs.
Understanding of AI ethics, bias, risk and output evaluation frameworks.
Experience using Python based generative AI libraries such as Hugging Face Transformers, OpenVINO, Unsloth, llama cpp python, DSPy and PyTorch.
Experience working with structured and unstructured data, and strong data engineering capability for building reliable ETL pipelines.

efficiency in service delivery

The Data and Analytics Branch provides the evidence base to inform policies, programs and services through the safe and effective use of data. Job Title: Data Analyst & Reports Developer | Tableau & PowerBI
Ad Text:
About the Company

Our client is a leading organisation in the Financial Services sector undergoing a period of reporting transformation. With a supportive analytics leadership team and growing demand for insightful, high‑quality reporting, they are now looking for a Data Analyst & Reports Developer to join their team.

About the Role

This is a hands‑on data analysis & reports development role and stakeholder‑facing role, ideal for someone who enjoys solving business problems and bring both Tableau and Power BI experience.

You will sit between the business and technical teams, ensuring clear requirements, high‑quality delivery, and meaningful insights. You will contribute to both ongoing reporting needs and strategic uplift initiatives.
Contribute to both strategic reporting initiatives and tactical BAU deliverables.
Develop dashboards and data models in both Tableau and Power BI.
Write and maintain SQL queries, perform data validation, and apply sound data‑modelling techniques.
Act as a trusted partner between business and technology teams, ensuring clear communication and successful delivery.
 
Skills & Experience Required

Strong experience in both Tableau and Power BI (essential).
Solid SQL skills, including writing queries, validating data and building data models, and experienced in building data pipelines would be highly regarded.
Demonstrated ability to work directly with business stakeholders: confident, clear, and able to shape requirements.
Experience building reporting solutions that solve real business problems.
Comfortable working through ambiguity, particularly during technology transition phases.
Open‑minded, collaborative, and willing to adopt new approaches (ideal for someone without rigid, “fixed” ways of working).
Financial Services industry experience is highly desirable.


What's on Offer
An immediate 12 months' contract opportunity with potential of extension. A unique opportunity to influence a major platform decision.
A hybrid working model balancing 3 days in the office with 2 days at home.
Excellent exposure to both reporting operations and long‑term strategic uplift.
Supportive leadership and strong professional development environment.

Click on the ‘APPLY’ button or contact Angela Tan Jenkin on angela.jenkin@profusiongroup.com 

We are committed to providing a supportive culture and positively contributing towards creating diverse and inclusive workplaces for our candidates & clients. We invite candidates of all ages, genders, sexual orientation, cultural backgrounds, people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, and Indigenous Australians to apply.

About LEAP

LEAP is the leading provider of Legal Practice Management Solutions in the world and is part of ATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies. For more than 30 years, our curiosity and commitment to continual improvement has kept us reimagining productivity tools for lawyers and their staff to support our guiding purpose, to ‘Help lawyers who help people’. The market-leading software we develop, and support is used by more than 70,000 lawyers and their staff in small and medium-sized law firms.

Working alongside our international team of passionate high achievers, you’ll join a fast-growing technology business where things seldom stay the same for long. With more than 800 smart, caring and ambitious ‘LEAPsters’ working together across Australia, Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland, Poland and New Zealand, you’ll find yourself in good company here.

Meet the Global Business Systems team

We’re a fast growing business built on a foundation of cutting edge technology and our Global Business Systems Teams are the sharp minds and steady hands keeping us running smoothly and making sure we’re always one step ahead. 

Whether you’re keeping user’s technology up to date, using analytics to solve complex business problems, or digitising processes to improve the ways we work, our technology specialists are the forward thinking experts keeping the engine of our continued success running – and the success of our clients too.  

If you’re a tech-savvy critical thinker with big ambitions and a passion to make an impact, you’ll discover not just a fulfilling career, but the opportunity to redefine the world of LegalTech. 

What you'll do

As our newest Analytics Engineer, you’ll be designing and scaling LEAP’s new enterprise data platform and semantic layer - the foundation for consistent metrics, AI enablement, and trusted insights that guide decisions across Executive, Product, Marketing, and Finance. This is a hands-on, engineering-focused role where you’ll partner closely with our BI Manager and Insight Analyst to ensure that metrics are standardised and data is accessible, trustworthy, and ready for both dashboards and advanced analytics. 

To make this happen, you will:

Build and maintain scalable, governed data models in dbt/Snowflake that power cross-functional reporting and advanced analytics. 
Develop and extend the universal semantic layer, ensuring metrics are consistent, reusable, and ready for both BI and AI applications. 
Structure high-quality, well-documented data assets that serve as the knowledge base for AI agents, predictive analytics, and self-service BI. 
Optimise and manage data pipelines (Fivetran/dbt) for reliability, performance and incremental refresh. 
Collaborate with the Data & Insights Analysts to translate the Metrics That Matter, a unified KPI framework across functions, into scalable, governed data models within the semantic layer. 
Ensure data quality and trust through testing, monitoring, and documentation.  

What you'll bring

Proficiency in SQL and modern data modelling (dbt preferred). 
Hands-on experience with Snowflake (or other cloud data warehouses). 
Familiarity with Fivetran (or similar ELT tools). 
Proven ability to design reusable, scalable data models that drive business outcomes. 
Experience integrating multiple data sources (Salesforce, Zuora, product usage, financial systems). 
Proactive, detail-oriented, and able to balance speed with governance. 
Experience with version control systems (Git preferred) and familiarity with CI/CD practices. 

Consider it a bonus if you have: 

Exposure to BI/visualisation tools (Tableau, Power BI, or similar). 
Experience with Python for data processing or automation. 
Interest in AI/ML integration (no need to be an expert yet). 

You are the type of person who

Has a collaborative, proactive mindset and you’re comfortable working in a fast-paced, evolving environment. 
Has strong communication skills, able to translate technical concepts into business outcomes. 
Is a self-starter attitude with a willingness to learn, experiment, and take ownership of tasks. 
Is a team player who understands that diverse opinions make a team and the benefit of achieving goals and decisions together. 
Is curious - you're not afraid to ask questions, explore and share your thoughts and ideas.  

LEAP is an inclusive, people-first company committed to breaking down institutional barriers that keep people from reaching their potential. If you meet some, but not all the requirements above, we encourage you to still submit your application.

Why join LEAP?

Your work matters. Helping lawyers help people sits at the heart of everything we do. We solve real world problems that improve and support local, everyday law firms. So they can do their best work for the people in the communities they serve.
Make an impact. You won’t be another ‘cog in the wheel’ here. We give full trust and autonomy for you to be heard, to work on big & complex projects – and to make a real difference.
Work with a group of authentic, passionate people who love what they do.
Well-funded and global. LEAP is the leading provider of Legal Practice Productivity Solutions across Australia, Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland and New Zealand. We're part of ATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies.
Flexible and hybrid working. We'd like to find this person in Sydney, but we want you to work in a way that suits you and we're open to flexible arrangements that support you.
Grow your career with us. Our founder Christian Beck has been building legal tech businesses for over 30 years. There are opportunities galore to expand your career based on where your interests lie. We're not afraid to pivot based on market conditions - you will always have the opportunity to stay ahead of the curve and do your best work here.
Have fun with us. Celebrations. Socials. Sports teams. Access to sailing and yacht events.
We value your well-being - enjoy an additional paid wellbeing day every year, free gym membership, corporate dental plan and monthly massages in the office. We'll throw in a catered lunch and breakfast every week too. Oh and an on-site barista.
Access to LEAP Home - a program unique to LEAP to support you in buying your primary residence.

Opportunity to work with one of the largest General Insurer in Australia

Open to Sydney candidates only - Hybrid opportunity

Multiple positions available to work in our strategic projects.

About Hollard

Hollard Insurance is part of the Hollard Group of Companies and one of Australia’s largest general insurers Australia and New Zealand. We underwrite a broad range of general insurance products, including motor, home, contents, business, bicycle and pet, in proud partnership with some of Australia's biggest consumer brands and broker businesses. As an independent and privately owned company, we believe we can go further together – for our people, customers, communities and partners – through an innovative approach to providing insurance. 

Our state-of-the-art facilities in North Sydney reflect our commitment to providing innovative workspaces that support hybrid and remote work. 

Your Team

You will be part of a multi-disciplinary technology team, working closely with our customers (business, software vendors and partners) and strategic project teams.  The team is responsible for the development, implementation and maintenance of the Hollard Data Platform that support our customers through all aspect of the insurance value chain. The team is involved in all aspects from design through to testing, implementation, maintenance and support. You will be surrounded by data professionals that strive for excellence and implement data best practices to realise business value 

Your Role

Reporting to and working closely with the Data Platform Owner, your key focus area will be to support delivery of data engineering solutions in strategic projects and BAU. The role will cover the data life cycle end to end, from understanding stakeholder requirements and solution design through to user acceptance and post implementation testing.

Your duties and responsibilities

Providing support to the Platform Owner in order to clarify needs, determine impact, and define priority.

Developing good functional understanding of Hollard’s systems. 

Supporting the analysis, delivery and enhancement of business process initiatives.

Collaborating with business partners, technology groups, vendors, suppliers and business stakeholders from all levels of the organisation to gather and analyse end user data requirements.

Producing high quality business requirements documents that are clear and are easy to understand so that they can be implemented by the technical and vendor teams.

Analysing and defining data mappings and processing rules from Hollard Policy Administration System(s) and Claims Administration System(s) to Data Platform(s) and downstream systems including Finance.

Your knowledge and experience 

Demonstrated experience as a Technical Business Analyst or Data Business Analyst

Strong understanding of data structures and how these are used and manipulated to produce output to solve business problems.

Strong background in Insurance (General, Life, or Reinsurance) or Finance domain.

Experience working within Data and Finance projects with a strong understanding of finance operating environment and their data requirements desirable.

Hands on experience modelling for ODS data lakes, data warehouse, data marts, and enterprise big data platforms.

Strong SQL skills and Microsoft Azure, including Synapse Serverless, Notebook is desired.

Working at Hollard

At Hollard, you’ll discover an environment where you can truly make an impact. We offer the best of both worlds – the opportunity, agility and creativity of a company growing with scale, alongside a focus on becoming a catalyst for enduring, positive, social change. 

We’re a tight-knit team, where authentic voices and unique perspectives matter. We work supportively, collaboratively and inclusively to help shape our future and create shared value for our communities. 

Hollard proudly promotes flexible work including remote work, non-traditional work patterns, and work-family balance. We’re also unapologetically committed to creating a workplace that values your diversity with a true sense of inclusion.  We actively seek to hire for your different lived experiences, including as it relates to disability, ethnicity, faith, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, gender diversity, sexual orientation, age, neurodiversity. 

We’re building something special. Working closely with our industry partners to reshape insurance for the better, we’re people changing insurance. 

Please note:  

Even if you don’t meet all our selection criteria, we encourage you to apply.  

A full background check will be completed on the successful applicant. 

Visit the Hollard careers page to learn about how Hollard will collect, store and handle your personal information.  

We are NOT engaging Recruitment Agencies for this role and ask agencies to respect our policy of no unsolicited contact regarding advertised vacancies.

About the role

At BOQ Group, we’re building a simpler, more resilient bank, and strong risk capability is at the heart of that transformation. As a Senior Analyst in Line 1 Risk, you’ll play an important role in helping our teams embed proactive, thoughtful and practical risk management every day. This role is all about empowering the business to make confident decisions that balance opportunity with strong, safe outcomes for our customers and the Group.

You’ll work closely with Business Unit leaders and partner with Group functions to ensure our risk practices align with BOQ Group’s Risk Management Strategy and standards. Your work will help uplift controls, strengthen our risk culture and ensure we’re meeting regulatory expectations. From providing day‑to‑day risk advice to supporting change assessments, designing and enhancing controls, analysing key trends, or assisting with governance and reporting, you’ll be a trusted voice that helps the organisation understand risk and respond to it effectively.

This role is hands‑on and collaborative, and you’ll contribute to activities that support the Group’s control environment, including risk in change assessments, management of issues and events, developing and updating risk profiles, and supporting the delivery of BOQ Group’s remedial actions.

You’ll also play a part in building capability across the business by sharing knowledge, offering guidance and supporting teams to lift their confidence in core risk practices.

About you

You’re someone who enjoys working in a dynamic environment where risk management genuinely shapes the way we operate. You bring curiosity, strong analytical thinking and a commitment to enabling better outcomes for our customers and our people.

You’re comfortable engaging across different teams, offering clear and pragmatic advice, and supporting stakeholders to understand risks, obligations and controls in a way that feels accessible and constructive.

Your background includes experience in risk management within financial services or a related environment, and you understand how to navigate regulatory expectations and non‑financial risk disciplines. You communicate clearly, think logically and pay close attention to detail. You enjoy unpacking complex issues, exploring root causes and designing solutions that strengthen control effectiveness. You also value collaboration and take pride in contributing to a positive team culture where continuous improvement is part of how you work.

If you’re looking for a role where you can influence meaningful change, deepen your expertise and help shape the future of risk at BOQ Group, this is an opportunity to make a real impact.

About us

BOQ Group is a truly unique group of challenger brands with a purpose – to provide a genuine alternative to Australian financial services for customers and employees.

Our family of brands (Bank of Queensland (BOQ), ME Bank, Virgin Money Australia, BOQ Specialist), each come with their own defined customer audience and brand personality, but share one goal – to build social capital through banking. That’s creating trust with customers, exploring staff potential and believing that tiny gestures and big ideas can change the world for communities.

BOQ Group’s inclusive vision is to foster a workspace that values and leverages difference and creates new possibilities, a place where our people feel confident to bring their best selves to work every day. We embrace difference and believe that our workforce should reflect the customers and communities that we serve.

Since 2021, BOQ Group is recognised as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA).

In 2023, we successfully implemented an innovative Reconciliation Plan, driving positive change and promoting inclusivity across BOQ Group.

Our perks

At BOQ Group, we are passionate about creating an exceptional work environment that nurtures both your professional and personal growth.

Our comprehensive benefits package is designed to enhance your well-being, provide financial security, and foster a sense of community and inclusion. Here are just some of the fantastic perks you can enjoy as part of our team:

Flexible working arrangement - Balance your work and personal life with ease.

Discounted financial products - Enjoy exclusive rates on our financial services across the Group.

Salary sacrificing options - Maximise your take-home pay with our salary packaging options.

Paid parental leave with no minimum requirements - Spend quality time with your new family member without any worries.

Purchase additional annual leave - Need more time off? You can buy extra leave days.

Discounted private health insurance plan - Take care of your health with our special rates.

Employee Assistance Program (EAP) - Access confidential support for personal and professional challenges for you and your family

Access to employee network groups - Connect with peers through our First Nations Reconciliation, LGBTQIA+, Multicultural, Gender, Early Careers, and accessibility groups.

Pride in Diversity membership - We are proud members of Pride in Diversity and actively participate in the Australian Workplace Equality Index.

We are committed to creating a workplace where everyone feels valued and supported. Join us and be part of a company that truly cares about its people and community!

How to apply

To apply for this role, follow the links.

BOQ Group is committed to diversity and an inclusive workforce. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People are encouraged to apply.

We celebrate, value and include people of all backgrounds, gender and expressions, sexualities, cultures, bodies and abilities. When you apply, you are welcome to tell us the pronouns you use and please let us know any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

These checks may include, but are not limited to identity, verification, reference checks, criminal background checks, immigration checks, verification of academic qualifications, bankruptcy checks.

About GSK

GSK is a global biopharma company with a special purpose – to unite science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together. Our success depends on our people. We want GSK to be a place where people feel inspired, encouraged and challenged to be their best, where they can grow and thrive.

If you share our ambition, join us at this exciting moment as we get Ahead Together.

 About the role

We are seeking a Customer Insights & Analytics Manager to transform customer‑level data into clear, actionable insights that directly shape our commercial and patient strategies in Australia.

This role is based at our Abbotsford office, with hybrid working arrangements available to support flexibility.

In this senior individual contributor role, you will lead customer targeting, segmentation, territory design, and data‑driven recommendations that improve resource planning and engagement effectiveness. You will work closely with Sales Excellence, Marketing, Market Access, Reporting, and our external data partners to turn complex data into simple, strategic actions.

Your role will be varied and will include:

Leading customer targeting, profiling and segmentation
